translated: Friberg, Gustaf Bertil, provincial physician, Vaggeryd, b. 27/10/97 in Sala to the first city physician Carl F. and Anna Åberg. Married in 1937 to dentist Margit Lindroth. Children: Tom b. 1942, Ann b. 1945. - Completed secondary school in 1916 and medical degree in 1920 at Uppsala University, medical doctorate in Stockholm in 1926. Assistant physician at Sala hospital in 1926, surgical department at Academic Hospital in 1926-1927, resident physician at Gävle hospital in 1927, assistant physician at Gothenburg Women's Clinic in 1927-1928, acting junior physician at Blekinge 1st Sanatorium in Fur and resident physician, Bollnäs, Avesta and Södertälje hospitals in 1928, acting second junior physician at Västervik hospital in 1929, second resident physician there in 1929-1930, first resident physician in 1930-1932, acting district physician in Ramnäs and M^elderud in 1932-1933, acting second physician at S:t Jörgen's hospital and acting assistant physician at Gothenburg epidemic hospital in 1933, acting chief city physician of Enköping in 1933-1938, district physician in Vaggeryd since 1938, railway physician for Skillinga-ryd-Månsarp and Vaggeryd-Fredriksdal since 1946. Military physician in the Reserve from 1929.
